Initialize agtrace by detecting provider configurations, creating the database, and scanning logs.

This is typically the first command to run. It will:
  1. Auto-detect installed providers (Claude Code, Codex, Gemini)
  2. Create the SQLite index database
  3. Scan and index existing session logs

Use --refresh to force a re-scan even if recently indexed.

Usage: agtrace init [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --data-dir <DATA_DIR>
          Directory for agtrace database and configuration
          
          [default: ~/.agtrace]

      --refresh
          Force re-scan even if recently indexed

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format for command results
          
          [default: plain]
          [possible values: plain, json]

      --log-level <LOG_LEVEL>
          Logging verbosity level
          
          [default: info]
          [possible values: error, warn, info, debug, trace]

      --project-root <PROJECT_ROOT>
          Override project root directory (defaults to current directory)

      --all-projects
          Operate on all indexed projects instead of current project only

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
